description:
What is a Customer Service Representative or Patient Advocate for IME Guards?  
A patient advocate for IME Guards will accompany a claimant (injury victim) during a medical appointment given by a doctor hired by a defense lawyer in a lawsuit. The appointments take place mostly in the Bronx, Westchester, Brooklyn, Queens and Manhattan.

What qualities does a Patient Advocate possess?

* Patient, empathetic, and passionately communicative;
* Detail-oriented;
* Punctual and professional;
* Assertive but not contentious;

Responsibilities

* Meet the claimant at doctor’s office;
* Make a detailed hand-written record of the IME;
* Create a computerized report of the IME; and
* Submit the report in a timely manner.

Requirements

* Strong communication and listening skills;
* Proficient with Microsoft Word;
* Customer orientation and ability to adapt/respond to different types of personalities;
* High school diploma or higher;
* Owns a car, not required but a big plus; and
* Fluent Spanish is not required but a huge plus;

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time

Pay: $45.00 - $55.00 per hour

Shift:

* Day shift

Education:

* High school or equivalent (Preferred)

Language:

* Do you speak fluent Spanish (Preferred)

License/Certification:

* driver's license and your own car (Preferred)

Work Location: In person
